Mainsail Art Festival: The 47th annual festival features national artists, musicians and culinary artists. It has been named one of the “100 Best Art and Design Shows” in the nation. Pets and coolers are not allowed. Free. 9 a.m.-6 p.m. Saturday, 10 a.m.-5 p.m. Sunday. Vinoy Park, 501 Fifth Ave. NE, St. Petersburg. Bon Jovi: The Rock & Roll Hall of Fame and Songwriters Hall of Fame band performs. $15.75-$746.25. 8 p.m. Friday. Amalie Arena, 401 Channelside Drive, Tampa. 813-301-6500. Pier 60 Sugar Sand Festival: The festival celebrates Clearwater Beach’s two most notable natural assets: sugar sand and sunsets. More than 14 sand sculptors use 1,000 tons of Clearwater Beach sand to create a walk-through “Sandimals: An Animal Adventure”-themed art exhibit housed in a 21,000-square-foot structure. Free activities include a children’s play area, street performers, artisans, live entertainment, fireworks, sand-sculpting classes and the master sand-sculpting competition. Free; $12, 3 and younger free (walk-through). 10 a.m.-9 p.m. daily through April 24. 1 Causeway Blvd., Clearwater. 727-403-0517. STOMP: The international percussion ensemble that uses everything but conventional percussion instruments to create rhythm — matchboxes, wooden poles, brooms, garbage cans, etc. — takes the stage. $35-$100. 7:30-9 p.m. Tuesday-Wednesday. Ruth Eckerd Hall, 1111 McMullen-Booth Road, Clearwater. 727-791-7400. Martina McBride: The award-winning country music singer performs. $50 and up. 8 p.m. Thursday. Seminole Hard Rock Hotel & Casino, 5223 Orient Road, Tampa. 813-627-7625. Shamarr Allen: The lead vocalist and trumpeter of Shamarr Allen and The Underdawgs, who has collaborated with renowned artists such as Willie Nelson, Harry Connick Jr. and Lenny Kravitz, performs. $12-$15. 8 p.m. Friday. Hooch and Hive, 1001 W Cass St., Tampa. 813-251-1234. Clearwater Art Walk: Stroll through downtown Clearwater while learning about the city’s public art scene in a docent-led public art walk. You will see at least 20 art installations including sculptures, murals, art wrapped signal boxes, pavement art and storm drain murals. The afternoon walks are coordinated to end just before the monthly Downtown District Sip and Stroll event. Get tickets at clearwaterartsalliance.org. $10 advance, $15 day of. 10:30 a.m. and 4 p.m. Saturday. Clearwater City Hall, 112 S Osceola Ave. 727-245-0077. American Stage in the Park: After a two-year hiatus due to the COVID pandemic, American Stage returns to the outdoor park stage for a presentation of Footloose — The Musical, based on the 1984 film of the same name. $21-$53. 8 p.m. Wednesday-Sunday. Demens Landing Park, 100 First Ave. SE, St. Petersburg. 727-823-7529. Todrick Hall: The singer who gained national attention on the ninth season of American Idol comes to St. Petersburg for a Ruth Eckerd on the Road performance. $79.75-$157.50. 8 p.m. Friday. Floridian Social Club, 687 Central Ave., St. Petersburg. 727-791-7400. Greater Seder: Greater Seder presents It’s Little Moses Mannie. Dinner includes Passover wine, matzo ball soup, chicken breast, dessert and drink. $65. 7 p.m. Saturday. Bryan Glazer Family JCC, 522 N Howard Ave., Tampa. 813-500-0621. Family Favorites Series: Tampa Theatre’s Family Favorites series celebrates kid-friendly classic movies brought back to the big screen. This portion features the 95-minute PG-rated comedy Hop, in which the next-generation Easter Bunny doesn’t want the job and runs away from home in hopes of joining a rock band. $10-$13, $8-$11 ages 2-12, $7-$10 members. 3 p.m. Sunday. Tampa Theatre, 711 N Franklin St. 813-274-8286. International Cuisine Food Truck Rally: Grab your foodie passport and go from truck to truck to try dishes from around the world. Free (food/drink additional). Noon-4 p.m. Saturday. 81Bay Brewing Co., 4465 W Gandy Blvd., Tampa. 727-487-3552. South Pacific: Love transcends the harsh realities of war and prejudice in this Pulitzer Prize-winning tale centered around two unlikely love affairs. The Rodgers and Hammerstein classic featuresa number of beloved songs, including Some Enchanted Evening. $35-$100. 7:30-10:30 p.m. Saturday. Ruth Eckerd Hall, 1111 McMullen-Booth Road, Clearwater. 727-791-7400. Chris Tomlin: The Tomlin UNITED Tour welcomes fans to worship together and experience the Christian artist’s music. $44.75-$129.75. 7 p.m. Tuesday. Amalie Arena, 401 Channelside Drive,  Tampa. 813-301-6500. Little Shop of Horrors: A sadistic singing dentist and an enormous people-eating plant combine to create this toe-tapping love story of nightmares. $32.50. 7:30 p.m. Wednesday-Friday, 2 and 7:30 p.m. Saturday, 2 p.m. Sunday. David A. Straz Jr. Center for the Performing Arts, 1010 N MacInnes Place, Tampa. 813-229-7827. 